OL,3,C'A restriction of truth': Medics speak
OL,4,Cout after guilty verdict
OL,6,FA Jersey paramedic and an ambulance
OL,7,Ftechnician say they are being
OL,8,F"restricted" from telling the truth
OL,9,Fafter both were found guilty of
OL,10,Ffailing to adequately care for a man
OL,11,Fin the moments before he died.
OL,13,FIn their first public statement since
OL,14,Fthe verdict and talking exclusively to
OL,15,FITV News, John Sutherland, 61, and Tom
OL,16,FLe Sauteur, 36, say their employer -
OL,17,FJersey Ambulance Service - has told
OL,18,Fthem not to speak about the incident,
OL,19,Ftheir suspension or the police
OL,20,Finvestigation that led to their charge.
