OL,3,C'A restriction of truth': Medics speak
OL,4,Cout after guilty verdict
OL,6,FIn response to Sutherland and Le
OL,7,FSauteur's comments, Kate Briden, Chief
OL,8,FOfficer for Jersey's Justice and Home
OL,9,FAffairs Department, says: "The two men
OL,10,Fare not being restricted from telling
OL,11,Fthe truth, in fact, they have already
OL,12,Fboth given evidence in the recent
OL,13,Fcourt case.
OL,15,F"They have been reminded of their
OL,16,Fcontractual obligations which state
OL,17,Fthey need the permission of their
OL,18,FChief Officer if they wish to speak to
OL,19,Fthe media. These are the same terms
OL,20,Fthat apply to every member of the
OL,21,Fpublic service.
